The paper discusses the use of mmWave frequencies for cellular networks, which falls under the category of network infrastructure (cs.NI) and multimedia (cs.MM). The paper also discusses the use of network coding, which falls under the category of information theory (cs.IT). The paper also addresses the issue of reliability in harsh propagation environments, which falls under the category of cryptography and security (cs.CR) and architecture (cs.AR).
